The paper deals with the reliability function of a communication channel, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The specific channel being studied is a broadcast channel, which falls under the category of communication networks (cs.COMM). The use of feedback in the channel also makes it relevant to the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also involves coding schemes and proof techniques, which are related to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG).
